A Lagos based non-profit organisation, Nirvana Sickle Cell Initiative has raised awareness on the Sickle Cell Disorder among secondary schools in Lagos State. The event is to commemorate the 2022 World Sickle Cell Day. The organisation, whose vision is to eradicate stigmatisation of people living with sickle cell, sensitised selected pupils in the Oke-Odo axis of the state on genotypes, sickle cell disorder, and its prevention.   Why I selected Shettima as running mate, by Tinubu     Ex-Chief Judge decries inhabitation of borstal homes by…     Hospital promises standard services   The sensitisation, which held at Unity School, Oke-Odo also featured free genotype testing for individuals. Founder of Nirvana Sickle Cell Initiative Modupe Babawale harped on the need to encourage early genotype testing, saying it will enable individuals make the right choice of partners. She maintained that it was derogatory to refer to people with Sickle Cell Disorder as ‘sicklers’, instead, they should be referred to as warriors since they are capable of living fulfilled lives with the right information on how to manage their health.